{{- end }}

## Getting Started

### Installation

```bash
# Clone the repository
git clone <repository-url>
cd {{ .Name }}

# Install dependencies
make deps
```

### Configuration

The application configuration is located at `config.yaml` in the project root. Update it with your settings:

```bash
# Edit the configuration file
vim config.yaml
```

### Build

```bash
# Build the binary
make build

# Or run directly
make dev
```

### Run

```bash
# Run the built binary
./build/{{ .Name }}

# Or use make
make run
```

## Development

### Available Commands

```bash
make help          # Show available commands
make build         # Build the binary
make dev           # Run in development mode
make test          # Run tests
make test-coverage # Run tests with coverage
make lint          # Run linter
make fmt           # Format code
{{- if .UseEnt }}
make ent-generate  # Generate Ent code
{{- end }}
make clean         # Clean build artifacts
```

### Testing

```bash
# Run all tests
make test

# Run with coverage
make test-coverage
```

{{- if .UseEnt }}

### Database Schema

Generate Ent schema code:

```bash
make ent-generate
```
{{- end }}

## API Endpoints

- `GET /` - Root endpoint
- `GET /health` - Health check
- `GET /version` - Version information
- `GET /api/v1/example` - Example endpoint

## Project Structure

```
.
├── cmd/{{ .Name }}/     # Application entry point
├── configs/           # Configuration files
├── data/              # Data layer (database, repositories)
├── handler/           # HTTP handlers
├── internal/          # Internal packages
│   ├── config/        # Configuration helpers
│   ├── server/        # Server setup
│   └── version/       # Version information
├── service/           # Business logic
└── Makefile           # Build automation
```

